# robotframework-stacktrace
a listener for rf >= 4.0 that prints a stack trace to console to faster find the code section where the failure appears.

## installation

```shell
pip install robotframework-stacktrace
```

## usage

```shell
robot --listener robotstacktracer <your file.robot>
```

documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) page for the package `robotframework-stacktrace` version 0.4.1, released on July 12, 2021. This package is a listener for Robot Framework (RF) version 4.0 or higher, designed to print a stack trace to the console to help users quickly identify the section of code where a failure occurs. It requires Python version 3.6 or higher. The package is licensed under the Apache Software License and is maintained by René Rohner (Snooz82) and mkorpela. The page also includes a warning for users with JavaScript disabled and those using unsupported browsers (specifically Internet Explorer 9 and below), advising them to upgrade for a better experience.
